**Learning Types**
- **Supervised Learning** — Trains on labelled input-output pairs so the model can predict outcomes on new data; covers both classification (e.g. spam detection) and regression (e.g. price prediction)
- **Unsupervised Learning** — Discovers hidden structure and patterns in unlabelled data using techniques like clustering, dimensionality reduction, and anomaly detection without predefined answers
- **Semi-supervised Learning** — Combines a small amount of labelled data with a large pool of unlabelled data, making it practical and cost-effective when full labelling is too expensive or time-consuming
- **Reinforcement Learning** — An agent learns optimal behaviour through trial and error by receiving rewards for good actions and penalties for bad ones; used in games and autonomous systems

