**Data Concepts**
- **Structured Data** — Neatly organised, tabular data with defined fields and schemas, such as sales records, spreadsheets, or sensor readings — easy to query and analyse
- **Unstructured Data** — Data with no predefined format including text, images, audio, and video; represents the vast majority of data generated in the world
- **Training / Validation / Test Sets** — The standard three-way data split: training teaches the model, validation tunes hyperparameters and prevents overfitting, and the test set gives an unbiased final performance evaluation
- **Bias (High)** — When a model is too simple to capture the underlying patterns in data, resulting in underfitting and poor performance on both training and new data
- **Variance (High)** — When a model is overly complex and memorises the training data too closely, performing well in training but poorly on unseen data — known as overfitting
- **Data Quality (4 Vs)** — Volume (enough data to learn from), Variety (diverse data reduces bias), Veracity (accuracy and trustworthiness of data), and Velocity (the speed at which new data is generated and processed)

